        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "There is currently a find() method, that will do a search based on the primary key, and return a rowset. A much more common use case when looking for rows by primary key it to find a single row, but there is presently no similar method that will return a single row. You either have to use fetchRow(), and specify the fields yourself, or use find() and then extract the first result (which there is currently no simple way to do, see ZF-1970).\n\nBased on the assumption that primary keys are always unique, if someone specifies a full key (i.e. there is a value for every PK column) there will only ever be one row returned. Therefore, could we add a new method that will only accept a full key, and will return a single row object?"
        },
