                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17373",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For anyone requiring this function now, you can extend Zend_Db_Table_Abstract with this:\n\n{code}\npublic function findRow()\n{\n\t$args = func_get_args();\n\tif (count($args) !== count((array) $this->_primary)) {\n\t\tthrow new Zend_Db_Table_Exception(\"Argument count does not match primary key column count\");\n\t}\n\t$rowset = call_user_func_array(array($this, 'find'), $args);\n\tif ($rowset->count()) {\n\t\treturn $rowset->current();\n\t} else {\n\t\treturn false;\n\t}\n}\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-01T08:06:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-01T08:06:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17387",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gbachelet",
                        "name": "gbachelet",
                        "displayName": "Geoffrey",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "bq. and then extract the first result (which there is currently no simple way to do\n\nyou could do:\n\n{code}\n$table->find($pk)->current();\n{code}\n\nwhich is simple enough in most time I guess.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gbachelet",
                        "name": "gbachelet",
                        "displayName": "Geoffrey",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-05T03:53:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-05T03:53:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17388",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Geoffrey, \nGood point. \"extract the first result\" isn't actually difficult at all, my mistake.\n\nI like your method, however I think it would still be beneficial to have the additional function, in order to enforce a full key, and ensure there's no possibility of multiple results.",
