                    "body": "Should findRow() ensure that exactly 1 row was returned?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-17T09:00:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-17T09:00:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33915",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I don't think this is a good addition.  For a few reasons.  If someone searches for something that produces more than a single row, taking the first off the stack is not good behavior b\/c the developer would never get to know how many actual rows were returned.  If someone can identify the behavior that would circumvent that ambiguity, ill reopen.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
